OL,3,CFraud victim's daughter calls for
OL,4,Cgreater protections against scams
OL,6,FThe daughter of a woman from Fleet who
OL,7,Flost #115,000 in a supermarket gift
OL,8,Fcard scam is calling for greater
OL,9,Fprotections against scams.
OL,11,FDebbie Horwood's 81-year-old mum,
OL,12,FValerie, was conned out of her live
OL,13,Fsavings after a fraudster pretended to
OL,14,Fbe an old school friend on social
OL,15,Fmedia and talked her into buying
OL,16,Fhundreds of gift cards.
OL,18,FValerie visited a number of
OL,19,Fsupermarkets to purchase the gift
OL,20,Fcards and Debbie says there needs to
OL,21,Fbe more awareness of this crime.
